18. Carbon Accounting & Reporting Analyst
SustainMetrics Advisory Services
Ortigas Center, Pasig City | REMOTE option available
SustainMetrics provides ESG consulting, carbon footprinting, and sustainability reporting services to corporations across Southeast Asia.
POSITION: Carbon Accounting & Reporting Analyst
Assist clients in measuring, managing, and reporting their greenhouse gas emissions in accordance with GHG Protocol and other international standards.
DUTIES:

Calculate Scope 1, 2, and 3 emissions for client organizations
Collect and analyze energy consumption, fuel use, and activity data
Prepare GHG inventory reports and CDP disclosures
Identify emission reduction opportunities and develop decarbonization roadmaps
Support clients with science-based targets (SBTi) development
Stay updated on carbon accounting methodologies and reporting frameworks

REQUIREMENTS:

Bachelor's degree in Environmental Science, Engineering, Accounting, or related field
1-3 years experience in carbon accounting, sustainability consulting, or corporate ESG
Understanding of GHG Protocol and carbon accounting principles
Proficiency in MS Excel; experience with carbon accounting software (SimaPro, carbon footprinting tools) is a plus
Strong analytical and communication skills
CPA or environmental certifications are advantageous

Employment: Full-time (Remote/Hybrid options)